{
  "stem": "8842.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They threw over the border many times a little baby, and so they could save them there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I met later a little-- a boy, a man now, that this is the only way-- this is the way he was saved of this whole atrocity.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that's, that's not now to mention.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In a routine of men and women had to go outside and work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were brigades.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And every brigade had its own job to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were also many people that were taken from the ghetto and moved onto another country, which we found out later some of them wind up to be in Latvia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of them wind up to be in Estonia and some in Poland or some in Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they used to bring also to our ghetto from other places for a while and then take them and kill them somewhere else, on, on, on a job.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you never saw them again coming back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "These kind of movements was a, a daily life-- became a daily life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But many, many steady people-- like my father used to work there in a brigade and used to go out early in the morning and come back at night.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He worked for a German-- for the Gestapo in the building where they li-- where they stayed, the Gestapo, as he was a butcher, if you recall.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was doing for them all the meats that they w-- that they need.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Somebody knew of him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that brigade was working only for that building-- for the cleaning and taking care of their, their rooms.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he wind up to be the in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes he used to steal in some little pieces of meat or something, things that fell off.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
